cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO

This paper is about video object segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel network architecture that uses both short-term and long-term memory to improve the performance of video object segmentation. This involves modeling fine-grained spatial-temporal interactions between local regions across neighboring frames and modeling the long-range evolution of objects. These tasks require machine learning techniques, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper's focus on video object segmentation suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics and Control), as this is an important task in robotics applications.
